There are three possibilities for passing the course:
a) Working as an assistant of a lecturer of a certain, usually a bachelor's level course. The tasks include carrying out seminars, evaluating and giving feedback to students' homeworks, etc under the supervision of the lecturer of the course.
b) Reviewing bachelor's thesis.
c) Preparing and teaching a part of the course or seminar including preparation of the teaching material in previous agreement with the program's manager.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The objective of the course is to provide knowledge and experience in university-level teaching. To apply the knowledge and skills acquired during the academic research or a certain course in a didactic context. To develop the skills of preparing studying materials, analyzing academic texts, argumenting and active listening.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After passing the course a master's/doctoral student knows the specificity of university-level teaching. A master's student is able to prepare and teach a lecture course or a seminar, evaluate students' independent work. A doctoral student is able to prepare or teach a lecture course or a part of it.
